I actually think this makes the game stronger.

Instead of trying to keep players busy with daily tasks, events, and timers, the **Academies become the entire game**. The challenge comes from mastering English, not from logging in every day.

I'd also keep **all Academies unlocked from the beginning**. That lets players learn what interests them. A child might start with Animals, while an adult preparing for IELTS might go straight to Academic Vocabulary.

The progression happens **inside** each Academy.

